summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed of conveyance from Clarence L. White and Erra W. White, his wife, dated the Sixth day of October, 1908, conveying to The City of Seattle, the following described property, to wit: Certain portions of the east one-half (1/2) of the southeast quarter (1/4) of the northeast quarter (1/4) of the southwest quarter (1/4) of Section two (2), Township Twenty-five (25) North, Range Three (3) East, W. M., all in The City of Seattle, Washington.
